OL,3,CSmell of cannabis 'night in, night
OL,4,Cout' at troubled Parc Prison, inquest
OL,5,Ctold
OL,7,FMr Gardner said was exposed to
OL,8,Fcannabis for "11 hours a night", and
OL,9,Fthat his headaches had been so severe
OL,10,Fhe'd been forced to stop on the M4
OL,11,Fmotorway due to a "severe nosebleed."
OL,13,FExplaining that simply moving to
OL,14,Fduties elsewhere wouldn't solve the
OL,15,Fproblem, the e-mail went on: "Why
OL,16,Fshould others suffer as a result of
OL,17,Fwhat the company has exposed them to?
OL,19,F"No matter who arrives (at the prison)
OL,20,Fthey pass comment on the smell of
OL,21,Fcannabis in the centre corridor.
