OL,5,Ctold
OL,7,FQuestioned by the lawyer representing
OL,8,FG4S -the company which runs Parc - Ms
OL,9,FLines acknowledged that drugs were "a
OL,10,Fmassive problem" in prisons everywhere.
OL,12,F"The drugs economy is worth millions
OL,13,Fin the prison system.
OL,15,F"I don't think you'd find any country
OL,16,Fthat wouldn't say drugs are a massive
OL,17,Fproblem."
OL,19,F'It's a very different picture to
OL,20,Fwhere we were ten years ago.
